text: Tulare ( ) is a city in Tulare County, California. The population was 68,875 at the 2020 census. The city is named for the currently dry Tulare Lake, once the largest freshwater lake west of the Great Lakes. The city is sixty miles north of Bakersfield, California. ==Famous people== *Devin Nunes (born 1973), former member of U.S. House of Representatives ==References== Category:Cities in California Category:Settlements in Tulare County, California
